Package hu.bme.mit.theta.core.type.rattype

Rational type and its expressions. Use RatExprs to create them. - RatType: the actual rational type - RatLitExpr: rational literal, e.g., 1%2 is 0.5 - RatNegExpr: unary minus - RatPosExpr: unary plus - RatAddExpr: addition - RatSubExpr: subtraction - RatMulExpr: multiplication - RatDivExpr: rational division - RatEqExpr: equal - RatNeqExpr: not equal - RatGtExpr: greater - RatLtExpr: less - RatGeqExpr: greater or equal - RatLeqExpr: less or equal
